TCS34725 colour sensor


This sensor measures luminance, INFRARED, RED, GREEN, BLUE light components of an object placed in front of it. It has an illuminating LED adjacent to the detector, and the reflected light is analyzed.

In the program , the red green and blue values are filled into separate lists and plotted side by side to show the variation. Depending on the object colour, the levels of R , G, B will vary.


Example.


A red object reflects red light and absorbs others. So you can see that the value of red is higher.



Example 2. Mixed colours


Cyan colour is a mix of two colours green and blue. So both these colours are reflected, but red is absorbed.
